body:
Use SVG for the high-level diagram so it displays correctly on dark themes. The old PNG with transparent bg did not show well in e.g. the Github default dark theme, making most text illegible. This takes advantages of the `prefers-color-scheme` CSS media feature.

Clean up diagram:
- Use SVG Firefox logo;
- Use sans-serif font iof. Helvetica;
- Do not use shadows in export;
- Center align some text and lines;
- Add a space between platform auth and superscript Δ for consistency;
- Make sure the lines are consistently in the background of perimeters.


How it looked before:
![image](https://github.com/AlfioEmanueleFresta/xdg-credentials-portal/assets/1408377/d0edc021-fcc4-47cc-a70f-6584c8e3601d)

How it looks now:
![image](https://github.com/AlfioEmanueleFresta/xdg-credentials-portal/assets/1408377/98be8b68-1505-4fca-80cd-fdc0d91c66cf)

![image](https://github.com/AlfioEmanueleFresta/xdg-credentials-portal/assets/1408377/46b0be88-e360-4526-a9ee-300e69c4b073)

If someone knows how to make the background colour transparent or match the Github background color, please let me know and I'll update the PR. For now, at least people using dark themes can read the diagram, and it should look nicer on high resolutions. As a bonus, the SVG is slightly smaller in size.
